p.START.body=The room is almost dark. There is a slightly open window, it is raining outside, and it is late at night. A neon light flickers above you, making a noise like a fly. With every flicker, the shadows shift half a millimeter. The terminal on the table is the only clear light: a cold rectangle that cuts your fingers when you get close.\nThere is a cruMpled sheet of paper on the floor. It has absorbed moisture in the corner and the paper has wrinkled. In one corner, there is a closed black notebook: matte cover, no title. It does not seem forgotten.\nIt seems to have been placed there. The cursor flashes on the screen with annoying regularity, an invitation, or a challenge...
